leads.lead_text: Capitulum solitary, 5–8 cm diam.; leaves lanceolate or elliptic, regularly serrate to serrulate; stems usually unbranched
Capitula 1–3, 3–5 cm diam.; leaves usually obovate or spathulate in outline, crenate or irregularly toothed to pinnatifid; stems often branched
